ClockFreq is StatusWare. That means you HAVE TO pay for it, depending on
your social status. Your social status is simply identified by the type of
cpu you were able to afford. Multiply the fourth digit of your cpu
with the MHz value of it and pay the resulting amount in $US. So what?
A poor 68000/7MHz can use this program for free (0*7=0),
a standard A1200 user has to pay $28 (2*14=28),
for a fat A4000/040/25MHz pay $100 (4*25=100),
and a proud 060 owner sends $300 (6*50=300).
(if you do not know the clock frequency of your Amiga, then use
